# Exchange Metadata Extraction Service — Frontend

A React-based web UI for the Capital One Exchange Metadata Extraction Service.  
Maps directly to **US-01** (File Upload UI) from the PRD and covers all user-facing steps in Section 7.

---

## Quick Start

```bash
cd metadata-extraction-ui
npm install
npm run dev
```

Open `http://localhost:5173`

---

## Project Structure

```
metadata-extraction-ui/
├── index.html
├── vite.config.js
├── package.json
└── src/
    ├── main.jsx              # React entry point
    ├── App.jsx               # Root — step state machine (Upload → Preview → Download)
    ├── styles.css            # Global design system (tokens, components)
    ├── components/
    │   ├── Header.jsx        # Sticky top nav with branding
    │   └── StepIndicator.jsx # 3-step progress bar
    ├── pages/
    │   ├── UploadPage.jsx    # Step 1 — drag-and-drop file upload
    │   ├── PreviewPage.jsx   # Step 2 — metadata table with inline edit
    │   └── DownloadPage.jsx  # Step 3 — JSON/CSV/PDF download + Exchange submit
    └── utils/
        ├── parser.js         # Client-side file parsing + metadata profiling
        └── downloader.js     # JSON, CSV, and PDF (print) download helpers
```

---

