| §3.1 | Multi-format upload (JSON, CSV, XML) | ✅ |
| §3.1 | File type detection & validation | ✅ |
| §3.1 | Field-level metadata extraction | ✅ |
| §5   | Full metadata schema (all 13 fields) | ✅ |
| §7   | 7-step user flow | ✅ |
| §6.1 | `/api/download/json` | ✅ (client-side) |
| §6.1 | `/api/download/csv`  | ✅ (client-side) |
| §6.1 | `/api/download/pdf`  | ✅ (print dialog) |
| §6.1 | `/api/exchange/submit` mock | ✅ |
| §3.2 | No auth / no persistence (Phase 1) | ✅ |

---

## Parser Capabilities

`src/utils/parser.js` runs entirely in the browser with no dependencies:

- **Type inference**: string, integer, float, boolean, date, object, array, null
- **Tag inference**: identifier, temporal, financial, personal, contact, categorical, metric, freetext, flag, geographic
- **PCI detection**: card, pan, cvv, expiry, account_num patterns
- **NPI detection**: ssn, dob, passport, license, patient patterns
- **Auto-descriptions**: plain-language field summaries from name + inferred tags
- **Stats**: null_count, unique_count, sample_values (up to 5)

---

## Design System

Dark-mode UI with:
- **Palette**: Deep navy `#0d0f14` background · Blue `#3b82f6` accent · Green `#22c55e` success
- **Type**: Syne (display headings) · Inter (body) · IBM Plex Mono (code/data)
- **Signature element**: Colored type pills per data type in the metadata table

---

## Adding Excel / Parquet Support

Install the `xlsx` library:

```bash
npm install xlsx
```

Then update `src/utils/parser.js`:

```js
import * as XLSX from "xlsx";

async function parseExcel(file) {
  const buf  = await file.arrayBuffer();
  const wb   = XLSX.read(buf, { type: "array" });
  const ws   = wb.Sheets[wb.SheetNames[0]];
  const rows = XLSX.utils.sheet_to_json(ws, { defval: null });
  const keys = Object.keys(rows[0] || {});
  return { rows, keys };
}
```
